* Running with gunicorn in production

  In production, I don't use the Flask dev server — I need =gunicorn=
  as the WSGI server. I add it to the same container and verify it
  can find my app:

  #+NAME: flask_gunicorn_check
  #+begin_src fixtureyaml :eval no-export
userfunction: gunicorn-check
project: examples/flask_application
func: alpine-python-user-venv
args:
  pip-packages: [flask, gunicorn]
chain:
  - with-file:
      path: /app/app.py
      source: "${ROOT}/examples/flask_application/app.py"
  - with-exec: [gunicorn, --check-config, "app:app"]
  - with-exec: [sh, -c, "echo gunicorn config ok"]
  - stdout
  #+end_src

#+RESULTS: flask_gunicorn_check
:results:
